Klinika uniwersytecka Addenbrookes naley do jednej z najwikszych w Wielkiej Brytanii, a jej charakterystyczny komin na stae wpisa si w krajobraz miasta. Cambridge is een stad (city) en district in Engeland in het graafschap Cambridgeshire, ongeveer 80 kilometer ten noordoosten van Londen. Cambridge beslaat een oppervlakte van 115.65 km en heeft ongeveer 120.000 inwoners, waaronder zo'n 22.500 studenten. De stad is vooral beroemd vanwege de universiteit van Cambridge, die met die van Oxford een van de twee belangrijkste Engelse universiteiten is, en tevens een van de beroemdste ter wereld. De verschillende colleges zijn over de hele stad verspreid, maar allemaal onderdeel van dezelfde universiteit. Cambridge is een stad met veel groen in parken en aan de rivier de Cam, waarnaar Cambridge genoemd is: Cambridge betekent brug over de Cam.

Cambridge ou Cantabrgia uma antiga cidade inglesa, sede do condado de Cambridgeshire. Situa-se a aproximadamente 80 quilmetros de Londres a 5212' de latitude norte e 007' de latitude leste. A cavaleiro de uma regio deprimida e pantanosa, de difcil circulao, e s margens do Rio Cam, afluente do Ouse, Cambridge domina uma das sadas naturais da rea. Da resultou sua primeira funo, a de porto fluvial, bastante importante para receber, na Idade Mdia, barcos martimos de pequeno calado. Sua situao geogrfica, tornou-a,no sculo XIII, sede da mais importante feira do pas. Graas ao intenso comrcio, representado pela exportao de ls, tecidos e produtos agrcolas, Cambridge enriqueceu, e, ainda no sc. XIII, assumiu novo papel: o de centro universitrio. Ao primeiro college (acomodao), o de Peterhouse, fundado em 1284, foram-se seguindo outros, chegando ao total de 31 colleges para homens e dois para mulheres. Alguns deles so especialmente afamados, como o Christ College, onde Erasmo ensinou teologia, o King's College, de belssima arquitetura, salientando-se sua capela orgival, do sc. XV, o Queen's College, o Trinity College, a que pertenceram Francis Bacon, Lord Byron e Sir Isaac Newton, Corpus Christi College e o Downing College. Ao contrrio de Oxford, sua tradicional rival, Cambridge foi muito pouco atingida pela industrializao, mantendo a atmosfera de cidade universitria em toda a sua pureza. A vida da cidade, praticamente, limita-se s atividades direta ou indiretamente ligadas populao estudantil, quase se despovoando nos perodos de frias escolares. Com os colgios recobertos de vegetao alinhados ao longo do rio, os verdes gramados e campos de esporte, a par da riqueza de sua arquitetura, Cambridge uma cidade extremamente bela, que o turismo tem sabido aproveitar de todas as maneiras. O censo de 2001 contou 108.863 habitantes em Cambridge, dos quais 22.153 eram estudantes. Em 29 de Abril de 2011, o prncipe William recebeu de sua av, a rainha Elizabeth II, o ttulo de duque de Cambridge, a poucas horas antes do seu casamento com Kate Middleton. Com isso, aps o casamento William e Kate foram reconhecidos como duque e duquesa de Cambridge. O ttulo de duque o mais alto da hierarquia da nobreza britnica, somente abaixo de reis e prncipes.

Horisonten i staden domineras av de sistnmnda tv byggnaderna. Staden r ocks hjrtat i "Silicon Fen", den brittiska IT-industrins centrum.

The city of Cambridge is a university town and the administrative centre of the county of Cambridgeshire, England. It lies in East Anglia, on the River Cam, about 50 miles (80km) north of London. According to the United Kingdom Census 2001, its population was 108,863 (including 22,153 students), and was estimated to be 125,717 in mid-2010. There is archaeological evidence of settlement in the area in bronze age and Roman times, and under Viking rule Cambridge became an important trading centre. The first town charters were granted in the 12th century, although city status was not conferred until 1951. Cambridge is most widely known as the home of the University of Cambridge, founded in 1209 and consistently ranked one of the top five universities in the world. The university includes the renowned Cavendish Laboratory, King's College Chapel, and the Cambridge University Library. The Cambridge skyline is dominated by the last two buildings, along with the chimney of Addenbrooke's Hospital in the far south of the city and St John's College Chapel tower. Today, Cambridge is at the heart of the high-technology centre known as Silicon Fen a play on Silicon Valley and the fens surrounding the city. Its economic strengths lie in industries such as software and bioscience, many start-up companies having been spun out of the university. Over 40% of the workforce have a higher education qualification, more than twice the national average. The green space of Parker's Piece hosted the first ever game of association football, and the Strawberry Fair music and arts festival is held on Midsummer Common. Cambridge is adjacent to the M11 and A14 roads, and is around 49 minutes from London Kings Cross by non-stop train, with other rail links to Norwich, Birmingham and elsewhere. In 2010, Forbes Magazine named Cambridge one of the "most beautiful cities in the world".

Cambridge on vanha yliopistokaupunki Englannissa noin 80 kilometri Lontoosta pohjoiseen. Se on ymprivn Cambridgeshiren keskus. Lhiseutua kutsutaan mys "Piisuoksi" sen ymprille kehittyneiden korkean teknologian yritysten ja tutkimuslaitosten takia. Vuonna 2001 Cambridgen 108864 asukkaasta lhes 22000 oli opiskelijoita ja kaupunki tunnetaankin ennen kaikkea siit, ett siell sijaitsee toinen Englannin kahdesta arvostetuimmasta yliopistosta, Cambridgen yliopisto. Yliopisto on hallitseva koko kaupungin rakenteessa. Keskustassa on lukuisia collegeja sek yliopiston hallintorakennuksia, joista osa on rakennettu jo keskiajalla. Toinen Cambridgen tunnusmerkki on Cam-joki, joka virtaa kaupungin lpi. Etenkin kesisin se on tynn turisteja erityisiss tasapohjaisissa punt-veneiss, joita tynnetn eteenpin pitkll, niin ikn punt-nimisell sauvalla. Joen takaranta on mys suosittu turistikohde. Parhaimman kuvan kaupungista yliopistokaupunkina saakin, jos kulkee edestakaisin joen yli eri collegejen lpi. Queens', King's, Clare, Trinity ja St John's Collegeilla on maata joen molemmin puolin. Muita mielenkiintoisia kohteita Cambridgessa ovat esimerkiksi yliopiston museo, Fitzwilliam Museum, King's Collegen kappeli, sek kasvitieteellinen puutarha.
